{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17600055","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17600055"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:01:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:01:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15604"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15604"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8295"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66643"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8295","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8295"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15604"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52096"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7005"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20024"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20025"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22237"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66643","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66643"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman undergoes a total thyroidectomy for a tumour. Microscopic examination of the thyroid specimen reveals the following histological features:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOptical clearing of nuclei (ground glass appearance)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPsammoma bodies\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENuclear grooves\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIntranuclear pseudoinclusions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENuclear overlapping\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Anaplastic carcinoma","Follicular adenoma","Follicular carcinoma","Medullary carcinoma","Papillary carcinoma"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe histological features described are pathognomonic for \u003Cstrong\u003Epapillary thyroid carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E. The key diagnostic features include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGround glass or \u0027Orphan Annie\u0027 nuclei (optical clearing) (Image 1)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPsammoma bodies (concentrically laminated calcified structures) (Image 2)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENuclear grooves\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIntranuclear cytoplasmic pseudoinclusions\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOverlapping nuclei\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese features distinguish papillary thyroid carcinoma from other thyroid neoplasms. \u003Cstrong\u003EAnaplasti\u003C/strong\u003Ec thyroid carcinoma shows marked cellular pleomorphism and necrosis. \u003Cstrong\u003EMedullary \u003C/strong\u003Ethyroid carcinoma has amyloid deposits and neuroendocrine features. \u003Cstrong\u003EFollicular \u003C/strong\u003Elesions (both adenoma and carcinoma) show follicular architecture without the distinctive nuclear features seen here.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Papillary thyroid carcinoma has distinctive microscopic features including nuclear clearing (ground glass/Orphan Annie nuclei), psammoma bodies, nuclear grooves, and pseudoinclusions.","These histological features help distinguish papillary thyroid carcinoma from other thyroid malignancies."],"references":["Shah JP. Thyroid carcinoma: epidemiology, histology, and diagnosis. Clin Adv Hematol Oncol. 2015 Apr;13(4 Suppl 4):3-6. PMID: 26430868; PMCID: PMC5526593","Kitahara CM, Schneider AB. Epidemiology of Thyroid Cancer. Cancer Epidemiol Biomarkers Prev. 2022 Jul 1;31(7):1284-1297. doi: 10.1158/1055-9965.EPI-21-1440. PMID: 35775227; PMCID: PMC9473679","Boucai L, Zafereo M, Cabanillas ME. Thyroid Cancer: A Review. JAMA. 2024 Feb 6;331(5):425-435. doi: 10.1001/jama.2023.26348. PMID: 38319329","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52096"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15604"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21274"},{"type":"media","id":"21275"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21274","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21274"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/QVrfs8mukyVyfE0kn5CvRtqiwvTu0G.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/QVrfs8mukyVyfE0kn5CvRtqiwvTu0G.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":600,"height":393}},{"type":"media","id":"21275","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21275"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/fy96zwxj1AtZRFHvZwpzTHdTEeiuS5.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/fy96zwxj1AtZRFHvZwpzTHdTEeiuS5.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":600,"height":394}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52096","links":{"sel